  "riddle": "1. Seek the page that tells of electric innovation and the company that changed the roads we travel. What year did this visionary enterprise first spark to life?\n\n2. Count the culinary havens that lie within close reach of the electric carmaker's abode — how many restaurants can you unearth?\n\n3. What bustling metropolis, known for its towering skyline, lists its highest natural point in an article? Discover the elevation noted in its overview.\n\n4. If you stand at the apex of this iconic city, how far above sea level do the streets sit? Ascertain this height from a trusted mapping source.\n\n5. Seek nature amidst the concrete — how many parks flourish within proximity of this urban center?\n\n6. Take your recent findings and amalgamate the elevation from clue 4 with the number of parks from clue 5. What new value emerges from this equation?\n\n7. The highest elevation noted in clue 3 holds a secret when its digits are reversed. What number does it transform into?\n\n8. Take the number of restaurants found in clue 2 and the height from clue 3. Subtract 400 from twice the height obtained in clue 4. The answer, when reduced, will yield a single digit: compute abs(clue 2 - clue 3) % 10. What is this final single-digit treasure?",
